Developer Map

This document helps developers and AI coding agents quickly understand how the system is structured and where to implement changes.

This prevents duplicate logic, architectural drift, and misplaced code.

AI agents must read this file before modifying the codebase.

Scheduler Architecture Rule

The Weekly Scheduler manages scheduled task placements, not deep task-definition authoring.

Use scheduler UI for:

scheduling

target assignment

ordering

deletion

viewing task details

Use separate template-management UI for:

creating reusable templates

editing sections/items

reordering checklist content

changing default display modes

AI agents must not merge template authoring and scheduler placement into one large modal unless explicitly requested.

High-Level System Flow

The application follows this flow:

User Interface (Next.js App Router)
        ↓
Server Actions / API Routes
        ↓
Authorization Layer (capabilities)
        ↓
Domain Logic (lib/)
        ↓
Supabase Database (RLS enforced)

Important rule:

Client components must never directly access privileged data.

All protected operations must pass through server-side logic.

