Permissions System

Authorization uses capabilities, not role checks.

Structure:

employee_roles
role_capabilities
capabilities

Helpers exist in:

lib/auth/

Example:

requireCapability("manage_tasks")

Avoid checking:

profiles.role === "admin"
Domain Logic Location

All domain logic should live in:

lib/

Structure:

lib/
  auth/
  notes/
  tasks/
  payroll/
  projects/

Server actions should call these helpers instead of embedding SQL directly.

Supabase Usage Rules

All database access must respect Row Level Security.

Never disable RLS.

Service role keys must never appear in client code.

Server-only access should use:

createAdminClient()

Client code should use the public client.

Migrations

All schema changes must use ordered migrations.

Location:

supabase/migrations/

Example naming:

010_task_assignments_rls_fix.sql
011_task_delete_support.sql

Never modify an existing migration after it has been applied.

Environment Variables

Local development uses:

.env.local

Common variables:

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY

The service role key must remain server-side only.

Deployment

Production runs on:

Vercel

Environment variables must be configured in Vercel settings.

After changes to env variables, redeploy the project.

